author: Universal Pictures
description:
Priany Hadiatmodjo has dedicated her career to shaping the next generation of leaders across entertainment and media. As Director of the NBCUniversal Page Program, she plays a huge role in launching careers at one of the industry’s most prestigious training grounds, guiding emerging talent as they take their first steps into the business.

Priany’s love of film began long before her career—early introductions to iconic movies like The Breakfast Club and Coming to America sparked her appreciation for storytelling and its ability to connect audiences across generations. That passion for cinema carries into her work, where she fosters opportunity, champions mentorship, and creates pathways for early career professionals.

In this episode of Seen on the Screen, Jacqueline Coley sits down with Priany to discuss the impact of film, the lessons she’s learned as a leader, and how NBCUniversal continues to create opportunities for future industry leaders.

Follow and listen to Seen on the Scr
title: Cultivating the Next Generation w/Priany Hadiatmodjo | Seen on the Screen with Jacqueline Coley
